### Compile LangGraph with InMemorySaver and Memory Store

Source: https://github.com/langchain-ai/langgraph/blob/main/docs/docs/concepts/persistence.md

This example illustrates how to set up and compile a LangGraph workflow using an `InMemorySaver` as a checkpointer and an `in_memory_store` (or `memoryStore` in TS). The checkpointer is vital for saving and restoring the graph's state across different conversational threads, while the memory store enables the persistence and retrieval of arbitrary information accessible across these threads. This setup is fundamental for building stateful conversational agents.

```python
from langgraph.checkpoint.memory import InMemorySaver

# We need this because we want to enable threads (conversations)
checkpointer = InMemorySaver()

# ... Define the graph ...

# Compile the graph with the checkpointer and store
graph = graph.compile(checkpointer=checkpointer, store=in_memory_store)
```

```typescript
import { MemorySaver } from "@langchain/langgraph";

// We need this because we want to enable threads (conversations)
const checkpointer = new MemorySaver();

// ... Define the graph ...

// Compile the graph with the checkpointer and store
const graph = workflow.compile({ checkpointer, store: memoryStore });
```

